isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

liquidate(bytes32,address,uint256).details: Public wrapper for _liquidate internal function.     * The caller needs to approve the closeAmount prior to calling. Will not liquidate more than is needed to restore the desired margin (maintenance +5%).     * Whenever the current margin of a loan falls below maintenance margin, it needs to be liquidated. Anybody can initiate a liquidation and buy the collateral tokens at a discounted rate (5%).

params.closeAmount: The amount to close in loanTokens.
params.loanId: The ID of the loan to liquidate.  loanId is the ID of the loan, which is created on loan opening.  It can be obtained either by parsing the Trade event or by reading  the open loans from the contract by calling getActiveLoans or getUserLoans.
params.receiver: The receiver of the seized amount.
